{"article_id":"ouwdpEGwzUGmj7wL","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"-- Updated at 4:20 pm ET .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"See end of post --","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"President Obama opened himself up to withering Republican attacks Friday via an off-hand statement","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"he made in a brief White House news conference .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Obama seemed to suggest","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that matters were going swimmingly for the private-sector part of the economy","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and that it was the reduction of government jobs","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that was the real problem .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Asked to respond to Republican charges","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"that he was blaming Europe 's economic policies for the alleged failure of his own domestic economic policies ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"Obama said :","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"`` As I 've said ,","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"we created 4.3 million jobs over the last two","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"( years ) ,","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"27 months , over 800,000 just this year alone .","depth":14},{"id":15,"text":"The private sector is doing fine . ''","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"Screech ! ! !","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"As soon as the president uttered those words ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"it was obvious he and his campaign would be hearing this line repeated back at them for a while , and not in a good way .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Anyway , Obama continued ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"apparently oblivious to the troubles","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"he had created for himself ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"adding context to his remarks .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"`` Where we 're seeing weakness in our economy have","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"( sic )","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to do with the state and local government , often times cuts","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"initiated by governors or mayors","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"who are not getting the kind of help","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"that they have in the past from the federal government .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"And who do n't have the same kind of flexibility as the federal government","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"in dealing with fewer revenues","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"coming in . ''","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"The way","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"many voters are feeling about public employees these days ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"that 's not necessarily an argument","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"likely to get a lot of sympathy .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"In any event , it was completely overshadowed by his `` the private sector is doing fine '' comment .","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"Obama was right","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"that the private sector has added jobs throughout the recovery","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"and that it has been the continual shedding of jobs by state and local governments","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"that has helped to restrain","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"to keep job growth .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Even so , progress in private sector jobs has cooled significantly in the last two months ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"with 87,000 non-government jobs created in April","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and 82,000 created in May .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Many people would n't describe those numbers as `` fine . ''","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"At a Capitol Hill availability with journalists , the first words out of House Speaker John Boehner 's mouth were :","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"`` Mr. President , I used to run a small business .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"And , Mr. President , take it from me ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"the private sector is not doing well . ''","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"He was followed by House Majority Leader Eric Cantor","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"whose first words were :","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"`` As the speaker said ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"we just listened to the president say","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"the private sector is doing fine .","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"I would say","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"Mr. President , are you kidding ?","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"Did you see the jobs numbers last week ?","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"The private sector is not doing fine . ''","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"Mitt Romney , on the campaign trail in Iowa , said of the man","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"he seeks to replace :","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"`` He said","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"the private sector is doing fine .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"Is he really that out of touch ? ''","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Mitch McConnell , like other Republicans , emailed journalists with the subject line","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"`` The private sector is doing fine ? ''","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"And , of course , Twitter was alive","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"with Republicans jumping all over Obama as well","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"which you can see for yourself at the # doingfine hashtag .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"It may have all been payback for the way","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Democrats ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"including Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"throttled Sen. John McCain in 2008","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"when , as the Republican presidential nominee he said , in the teeth of the Great Recession ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"`` ... The fundamentals of our economy are strong . ''","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Perhaps John Dickerson ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"who writes for Slate","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"and does political analysis for CBS News ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"made one of the more relevant points in a tweet","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"that seemed to suggest","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"that Obama has some high-profile company","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"when it comes to inducing winces in supporters","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"and feeding frenzies among opponents .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"`` 'private sector is doing fine ' = 'not concerned about the very poor . '","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Discuss . ''","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"In an attempt","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"to unring the bell","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"he struck earlier","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"with his remark","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"about the private sector being `` fine '' ,","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Obama took the opportunity of a photo op with Philippine President Benigno Aquino","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"to tell journalists","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"that he is not unmoored from reality","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"and indeed understands","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"that the economy as whole is n't `` fine . ''","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Here 's much of the president 's response to a reporter 's question :","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":191,"left":97,"right":190,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":97,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":189,"right":95,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":139,"right":188,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":139,"left":102,"right":138,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":98,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":4,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":5,"right":99,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":130,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":125,"right":129,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":112,"right":124,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":112,"left":109,"right":11